extends ../layout.jade

block content
  section.featured
        .container
          .row.mar-bot40
            .col-md-6.col-md-offset-3
              .align-center
                img(src="img/profile.jpg", alt="Patrick McKay", width=200).img-circle
                h2.slogan Welcome to McKay Development
                p
                  | This is the personal website and portfolio of Patrick McKay, a professional full-stack
                  | web developer in Denver, Colorado. Patrick graduated from the
                  | 10-week <a href="http://refactoru.com" class="white">RefactorU</a> dev bootcamp in Boulder in March of 2014, 
                  | and he is now pursuing his dream of a career building useful and modern websites for Colorado businesses.
                a(href="files/Mckay-Resume.pdf")
                  button(type="button").btn.btn-primary View resume  
      // services
  section#section-skills.section.pad-bot30.bg-white
    .container
      .row.mar-bot10
        .col-md-offset-3.col-md-6
          .section-header
            h2.section-heading.animated(data-animation='bounceInUp') Skills
      .row.mar-bot40
        .col-sm-4
          .align-center
            i.fa.fa-html5.fa-5x.mar-bot20
            h4.text-bold HTML5 / CSS3
            ul.align-left.move-right
              li.mar-bot5 Front-end markup with modern HTML elements and the latest CSS styling.
              li.mar-bot5 Comfortable hand-coding CSS or using popular CSS frameworks such as Twitter Bootstrap, Foundation, and SemanticUI.
              li.mar-bot5 CSS pre-processors including LESS, SASS, Compass, and Stylus.
        .col-sm-4
          .align-center
            i.fa.fa-code.fa-5x.mar-bot20
            h4.text-bold Javascript
            ul.align-left.move-right
              li.mar-bot5 Strong knowledge of Object Oriented (OO) Javascript programming, MVC, and RESTful architecture.
              li.mar-bot5 Skilled in using jQuery and AJAX to build highly interactive front-end designs.
              li.mar-bot5 Knowledgeable in modern front-end Javascript libraries and frameworks including AngularJS, KnockoutJS, and Handlebars.  
        .col-sm-4
          .align-center
            i.fa.fa-desktop.fa-5x.mar-bot20
            h4.text-bold Back-end Development
            ul.align-left.move-right
              li.mar-bot5 Back-end development using NodeJS, ExpressJS, MongoDB/Mongoose, and JADE. 
              li.mar-bot5 MEAN (Mongo, Express, Angular, Node) stack.
              li.mar-bot5 Passport authentication and oAuth 2.0.
              li.mar-bot5 Jasmine unit-testing.
              li.mar-bot5 Also proficient in basic PHP and MySQL.
  section#testimonials.section(data-stellar-background-ratio='0.5')
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          .align-center
            .testimonial.pad-top40.pad-bot40.clearfix.dim-background
              h5
                | "[Patrick has] exercised competence in all areas presented and embraced the culture of learning in development. 
                | [He] combine[s] technical skills with personal interests with a rare spontaneity and ease." 
              br
              span.author
                | â€” RAINE LOURIE 
              br
              span.author 
                | RefactorU Instructor
  
  // about
  section#section-about.section.appear.clearfix
    .container
      .row.mar-bot20
        .col-md-offset-3.col-md-6
          .section-header
            h2.section-heading.animated(data-animation='bounceInUp') About Patrick
            p
              | Passionate junior-level developer specializing in Javascript and modern web frameworks.
            a(href="files/Mckay-Resume.pdf")
                  button(type="button").btn.btn-primary View full resume  
      
      .row.align-center.mar-bot40
        .col-md-6
          p.align-left
            | I have always had a passion for technology and the Internet, and my first career plan was to become an internet lawyer who could represent tech companies and help foster a legal environment which enabled others to innovate online. 
          p.align-left
            | After graduating from law school in 2012, I worked for nearly a year as an attorney practicing civil litigation and criminal defense at a small Denver law firm. 
          p.align-left
            | While I enjoyed working as a lawyer, I ultimately decided it was not a viable long-term career. I decided instead to pursue my interest in technology from the creative side rather than the legal side, and actually become a developer myself. I left my law job in November of 2013, and have been pursuing a career in web development ever since.

        .col-md-6
          p.align-left
            | To jump-start my new career, I attended the ten-week RefactorU development bootcamp program in Boulder from January to March of 2014. The course consisted of 40+ hours per week of in-class instruction and programming exercises, employing many of the hottest upcoming web technologies. 
          p.align-left    
            | During the course, I designed and built several complete applications with both client-side and server-side components, and had the opportunity to explore a number of Javascript libraries, frameworks, tools, and build systems. 
          p.align-left
            | Though it was not part of the formal curriculum, I began to learn AngularJS for my final project and I have been learning more about that exciting framework (as well as gaining a working knowledge of PHP and MySQL) since completing the RefactorU course. 
  // /about
  // spacer section:stats
  section#parallax1.section.pad-top40.pad-bot40(data-stellar-background-ratio='0.5')
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          .align-center
            .testimonial.pad-top40.pad-bot40.clearfix.dim-background
              h5
                | As part of the RefactorU course, Patrick developed a number of functional web apps demonstrating a wide variety of front-end and back-end development skills.     
  // section works
  section#section-works.section.appear.clearfix
    .container
      .row.mar-bot40
        .col-md-offset-3.col-md-6
          .section-header
            h2.section-heading.animated(data-animation='bounceInUp') Portfolio
            p
              | See below for examples of web apps I have developed. Click the buttons to filter by the category of project.
      .row
        nav#filter.col-md-12.text-center
          ul
            li
              a.current.btn-theme.btn-small(href='#', data-filter='*') All
            li
              a.btn-theme.btn-small(href='#', data-filter='.frontend') Front-end
            li
              a.btn-theme.btn-small(href='#', data-filter='.node') Node.js apps
            //- li
            //-   a.btn-theme.btn-small(href='#', data-filter='.php') PHP
            li
              a.btn-theme.btn-small(href='#', data-filter='.other') Other
        .col-md-12
          .row
            #3.portfolio-items.isotopeWrapper.clearfix
              // Begin portfio list
              
              each item in portfolioItems
                article.col-md-4.isotopeItem(class=""+item.filter+"")
                  .portfolio-item
                    img(src="img/portfolio/"+item.image+"")
                    .portfolio-desc.align-center
                      .folio-info
                        h5
                          a(href="/projects/"+item.url+"") #{item.title}
                          p #{item.category}
                        a.fancybox(href="img/portfolio/"+item.image+"")
                          i(data-toggle='tooltip', title='View screenshot').fa.fa-search-plus.fa-2x.show-tooltip.mar-bot10
                        p #{item.shortDescr}
                        .row
                          .col-sm-4.align-center
                            if (item.github != "")
                              a(href=""+item.github+"")
                                i(data-toggle='tooltip', title='View code on Github').fa.fa-code.fa-2x.show-tooltip
                          .col-sm-4.align-center
                            a(href="/projects/"+item.url+"")
                              i(data-toggle='tooltip', title='View project details').fa.fa-list-alt.fa-2x.show-tooltip                    
                          .col-sm-4.align-center
                            if (item.demo != "")
                              a(href=""+item.demo+"")
                                i(data-toggle='tooltip', title='View live demo').fa.fa-play-circle.fa-2x.show-tooltip
      
                 //End portfolio list

  section#parallax2.section.parallax(data-stellar-background-ratio='0.5')
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          .align-center
            .testimonial.pad-top40.pad-bot40.clearfix.dim-background
              h5
                | In addition to programming, Patrick enjoys hiking, skiing, HDR landscape photography, video editing, and flying video-piloted remote control airplanes.   
 
  // contact
  section#section-contact.section.appear.clearfix
    .container
      .row.mar-bot40
        .col-md-offset-3.col-md-6
          .section-header
            h2.section-heading.animated(data-animation='bounceInUp') Contact me
            p
              | If you are interested in hiring me either for a full-time job or a freelance / contract gig, please submit the contact form below.
            p
              | You can also contact me by phone at (303)-809-3613 or email at <a href='mailto:patrick@fairusetube.org'>patrick@fairusetube.org</a>.
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          #contact-form.cform
            #sendmessage.contact-status.alert.alert-success
              | Your message has been sent. Thank you!
            #messagefail.contact-status.alert.alert-danger
              | Something went wrong. Please try again.
            form#contactForm.contactForm(action='/contact/submit-form', method='post', role='form')
              .form-group
                label(for='name') Your Name
                input#name.form-control(type='text', name='name', placeholder='Your Name', data-rule='maxlen:4', data-msg='Please enter at least 4 chars')
                .validation
              .form-group
                label(for='email') Your Email
                input#email.form-control(type='email', name='email', placeholder='Your Email', data-rule='email', data-msg='Please enter a valid email')
                .validation
              .form-group
                label(for='subject') Subject
                input#subject.form-control(type='text', name='subject', placeholder='Subject', data-rule='maxlen:4', data-msg='Please enter at least 8 chars of subject')
                .validation
              .form-group
                label(for='message') Message
                textarea.form-control(name='message', rows='5', data-rule='required', data-msg='Please write something for me')
                .validation
              button.btn.btn-theme.pull-left(type='submit') SEND MESSAGE
        // ./span12